encoding_desc.currency: The currency of the prices returned. `FRF` corresponds to french francs.
encoding_desc.high_price_c: The most expensive items in the catalogue, in constant 1900 francs. In the whole API, the `_c` suffix indicates that a price is expressed in constant 1900 francs.
encoding_desc.high_price_items_c: The most expensive items in the catalogue. Each item's `@xml:id` is associated to its price, in constant francs.
encoding_desc.item_count: The number of manuscripts for sale in the catalogue.
encoding_desc.low_price_c: The least expensive item's price, in constant 1900 francs.
encoding_desc.mean_price_c: The average price for a catalogue item, in constant 1900 francs.
encoding_desc.median_price_c: The median price for a catalogue item, in constant francs.
encoding_desc.mode_price_c: The mode price (the price that appears the most often in a catalogue)For an item, in constant francs.
encoding_desc.sell_date: The year of the sale presented in the catalogue.
encoding_desc.title: The title of the catalogue, and, by extension, of the sale.
encoding_desc.total_price_c: The sum of each item's price, in constant francs
encoding_desc.variance_price_c: The variance of the prices inside the catalogue.
